Learning R through blogging: a journey into the tidyverse

Félix Luginbühl

Juillet 07, 2018

I was doing an internship at the Embassy of Switzerland in Guatemala

but missing the cultural life of Geneva

So I started a blog about R

to investigate important questions

Is Marvel more successful at the box office than DC Comics?

But taking into account inflation

Which chapter of 1984 is the darkest?

Which countries has James Bond visited?

Which tennis player is the most popular?

Then I created my first package

Which now looks like this

And developped a seconde package

It was then time to go interactive

and making interactive maps

Then I tested XGBoost

Modeled for exploratory analysis

Made some forecasting on Swiss data

And finally competed on Kaggle

In summary

Thank you for your attention!
